00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:00,938
In JavaScript

2
00:00:01,075 --> 00:00:03,850
functions are one of the most fundamental concepts

3
00:00:04,162 --> 00:00:06,650
serving as building blocks for any program

4
00:00:07,625 --> 00:00:11,075
A function is a block of code designed to perform a specific task

5
00:00:11,438 --> 00:00:13,325
executed when something invokes it

6
00:00:14,287 --> 00:00:19,587
Learning how to define and invoke functions effectively allows developers to modularize their code

7
00:00:19,875 --> 00:00:22,425
making it reusable and easier to debug

8
00:00:23,438 --> 00:00:26,175
Functions can take parameters and return values

9
00:00:26,450 --> 00:00:29,300
enabling them to process inputs and give outputs

10
00:00:30,413 --> 00:00:33,938
JavaScript supports both function declarations and expressions

11
00:00:34,312 --> 00:00:35,888
enhancing its flexibility

